              "text": "CLIENT:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x1",
              "text": " Etienne Cootjans\n",
              "marks": []
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x2",
              "text": "CLIENT INTEL:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x3",
              "text": " Multidisciplinary Designer; Co-founder of Plant Based Gallery\n",
              "marks": []
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x4",
              "text": "SUBJECT:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x5",
              "text": " Three-Piece Suit\n",
              "marks": []
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x6",
              "text": "APPROACH:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x7",
              "text": " In collaboration with Etienne Cootjans, we sought to highlight the fusion of military apparel influences and the intricate tailoring of his three-piece suit design. Drawing inspiration from the historical interplay between military uniforms and civilian fashion, we conceptualized a visual narrative where the suit's complex patterns and bold materials serve as a form of camouflage. This approach underscores the idea that even the most elaborate designs can seamlessly blend into their surroundings, reflecting the duality of visibility and subtlety. The resulting imagery captures the essence of formal wear's evolution, paying homage to its martial roots while celebrating contemporary artistry",
              "marks": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "images": [
