            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x1",
              "text": " Joep Hijwegen\n",
              "marks": []
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x2",
              "text": "CLIENT INTEL:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x3",
              "text": " Photographer and co-founder of Kaijo Studio, known for crafting layered, cinematic imagery that sits between observation and orchestration\n",
              "marks": []
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x4",
              "text": "SUBJECT:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x5",
              "text": " <em>Glass & Steel</em> — portrait series\n",
              "marks": []
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x6",
              "text": "APPROACH:",
              "marks": ["strong"]
            },
            {
              "_type": "span",
              "_key": "span0x7",
              "text": " In <em>Glass & Steel</em>, Joep turns his lens toward the face—not as subject, but as surface. Eyes refract behind curved glass; lips soften into chrome reflections. Flesh becomes unfamiliar, reframed through the language of metal, mirror, and distortion. The series drifts between warmth and cold, intimacy and detachment—offering a vision of beauty that feels both ancient and entirely new. Expressions are fractured, refracted, veiled by the textures of industry and ornament, as if the human form were remembering or rehearsing a future version of itself.",
              "marks": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "images": [
